SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man was killed Thursday when the car he was driving crashed 
into a parked car in East San Diego, a San Diego police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim reportedly fell asleep while driving east on Home Avenue about 12:40 
a.m., Sgt. Mike Healey said. The car veered across the double-yellow line and 
smashed into a car parked along the north curb, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center, where he was pronounced 
dead. 
</P>
<P>
Healey said the coroner's office has been unable to determine the victim's 
identity. 
