<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTERS PLAY KEY ROLE IN CONSERVATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Certain animals of the wilderness are hunted and harvested at certain times of 
the year to allow humans a variety of game and to keep a balanced reproductive 
population of that species. As for domestic livestock, it's slaughtered 
according to demand. We can find domestic animals prepackaged for purchase, no 
feelings felt for the animal we never saw. For the hunter, game is a variety of 
meat. Deer are not killed daily like livestock. 
</P>
<P>
As for cruelty, it happens all the time all over the world. Wild and domestic 
animals are abused, maimed and driven out constantly, with or without the 
hunter. Cruelty to animals is something that can be caused by nature itself. 
</P>
<P>
JEFF STATZ, North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
