<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"They are depicting Arabs in a very derogatory manner -- as conniving, with 
hook noses, as ugly -- and this image has been haunting the Arab community." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Terri Ahwal, board member of the Detroit Arab-American Anti-Discrimination 
Committee, explaining the organization's boycott of Spencer Gifts Inc., a 
retail chain that is selling Halloween masks that look like PLO leader Yasser 
Arafat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
