<TEXT>
<P>
Nikolaus Lehnhoff, who created and produced the San Francisco Opera's "Ring of 
the Nibelung" four years ago, has pulled out of the company's planned 1990 
revival of the Wagner cycle because of what he termed an unworkable rehearsal 
schedule. Lehnhoff, in a letter to company general director Lofti Mansouri, 
said the schedule made it impossible to achieve "even a blueprint" of the 1985 
original production. The San Francisco Opera has booked four presentations of 
the four operas that make up the "Ring" next June and July. Mansouri said he 
would personally supervise the production team to mount the revival. ALEENE 
