WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LEBANON; 
</P>
<P>
3RD SWISS REPORTED TO BE KIDNAP VICTIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Swiss woman has been kidnaped in northern Lebanon, two days after the 
abduction of two Swiss Red Cross workers, the Foreign Ministry in Bern said. A 
ministry spokesman said the part-time flight attendant was abducted by armed 
civilians during a visit to the Mediterranean port of Tripoli. The woman's name 
and age were withheld at the request of her parents, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
