127 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELLIOTT ENDS HOLDOUT, SIGNS WITH SPURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN ANTONIO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
First-round draft pick Sean Elliott ended his holdout from the San Antonio 
Spurs Thursday and signed a five-year contract reportedly worth $9 million. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm excited to get it all over with," said Elliott, the No. 3 pick in last 
June's draft. "I knew all along that I'd be a Spur." 
</P>
<P>
The team did not announce terms of the agreement, but sources said the 6-foot-8 
forward from Arizona would receive $1.8 million a year, or $9 million over five 
years. 
</P>
<P>
"The speculation has been extremely accurate," said Bob Woolf of Boston, 
Elliott's attorney who negotiated the deal. 
</P>
<P>
Elliott signed in time for the Spurs exhibition season opener Saturday against 
Milwaukee in San Antonio. Asked if Elliott would play, Coach Larry Brown 
laughed, "Until his tongue hangs out." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
