NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Amateur Athletic Foundation's Board of Directors has authorized grants 
totaling $431,678 to 15 Southland youth organizations. 
</P>
<P>
The largest of the grants was to fund the AAF/Ladies Professional Golf Assn. 
junior golf program for a second year. A $76,778 grant was authorized for 
Reviving Baseball in Inner Cities, which last year provided teams for almost 
200 boys. 
</P>
