<P>
Corn Crop Up 51% From Year Ago: The Agriculture Department reported that 
farmers are harvesting a corn crop estimated at 7.45 billion bushels, up 51% 
from last year's drought-plagued harvest of 4.92 billion bushels. Moreover, the 
latest estimate, based on Oct. 1 field surveys, was almost 2% more than the 
7.32 billion bushels forecast a month ago. At 7.45 billion bushels, the harvest 
would be the largest since the 8.25 billion bushels of 1986. 
