<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IRVINE: The city's progressive policies are a hit in Manhattan, where The New 
Yorker magazine lauded the city for its ban on chlorofluorocarbons, admiringly 
calling the policy "idealistic, even quixotic." . . . Columnist Dianne Klein 
(B1) takes a less idealistic view of yet another Irvine venture -- the creation 
of a downtown with a grand boulevard like the Champs Elysees. 
</P>
