<HEADLINE>
<P>
BACKGROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Byrne, leader of the acclaimed rock band Talking Heads, has immersed himself in 
Afro-Latin music. He's compiled two anthology albums of Brazilian music and 
made a TV documentary about a Brazilian religion. His new album "Rei Momo" 
features backing by noted New York-based Latin musicians, many of whom are 
accompanying him on his first-ever solo tour. 
</P>
