<P>
253 ITALIAN TERRORISTS ACQUITTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A court today found 253 Red Brigade terrorists and other left-wing extremists 
innocent of charges of waging an armed insurrection against the state. 
</P>
<P>
The acquittals had been expected because of three previous rulings dating back 
to 1970 when Italian courts refused to accept the legal concept that domestic 
terrorism amounts to a political attack or the waging of war against the state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
